alog-split-01", "catalog", "fsa-owi-black-and-white-negatives", "main-catalog-split-01", "main-catalog"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2017758991/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/fsa/8b26000/8b26700/8b26745_150px.jpg#h=110&w=150", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/fsa/8b26000/8b26700/8b26745t.gif#h=111&w=150", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/fsa/8b26000/8b26700/8b26745r.jpg#h=469&w=640", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/fsa/8b26000/8b26700/8b26745v.jpg#h=750&w=1024"], "index": 5, "language": ["english"], "location": ["united states", "mississippi", "forrest county", "hattiesburg"], "mime_type": ["image/gif", "image/jpg", "image/tif"], "number": ["2017758991", "2017-08-09t10:25:01", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2017758991", "http://www.loc.gov/item/fsa1998017639/pp", "http://www.loc.gov/item/19871415"], "online_format": ["image"], "original_format": ["photo, print, drawing"], "partof": ["prints and photographs division", "lot 1631", "catalog", "american memory", "prints & photographs online catalog (library of congress)", "farm security administration/office of war information black-and-white negatives"], "score": 42.677074, "shelf_id": "LC-USF34- 000514-D [P&P] LOT 1631 (corresponding photographic print)", "site": ["pictures", "catalog"], "subject": ["mississippi", "nitrate negatives", "united states", "forrest county", "hattiesburg", "subsistence homesteads"], "timestamp": "2022-04-25T17:50:25.385Z", "title": "New house at Hattiesburg, Mississippi", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2017758991/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://lccn.loc.gov/2016655401", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2016655401/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.afc/afc2010039.afc2010039_crhp0110", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc2010039.afc2010039_crhp0110/", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc2010039.afc2010039_crhp0110_mv08/", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc2010039.afc2010039_crhp0110_ms01/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["crosby, emilye", "dahmer, ellie j.", "civil rights history project (u.s.)", "bishop, john melville"], "date": "2015-01-01", "dates": ["2015"], "description": ["Ellie Dahmer discusses her involvement in the NAACP and voting rights activism in Forrest County, Mississippi. She recalls her experiences in education, both as a student at local schools, Alcorn State University, and Tennessee A&I, and as a teacher in schools throughout Mississippi. Her career as a Forrest County election commissioner is also discussed. She speaks about her husband, fellow activist Vernon Dahmer, and remembers the night when Klu Kulx Klan members burned her home, killing her husband and injuring her children."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2022-10-04T17:35:53.116Z", "group": ["afc2010039", "catalog-split-14", "catalog", "civil-rights-history-project", "main-catalog-split-14", "main-catalog"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2016655401/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/afc/afc2010039/afc2010039_crhp0110/afc2010039_crhp0110_mv08.gif", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/afc/afc2010039/afc2010039_crhp0110/afc2010039_crhp0110_ms01.gif#h=150&w=116"], "index": 6, "language": ["english"], "location": ["united states", "mississippi", "hattiesburg"], "mime_type": ["image/gif", "application/pdf", "image/jpeg", "application/x-video"], "number": ["2020-01-23t09:39:29", "2016655401", "online resource"], "online_format": ["image", "pdf", "video"], "original_format": ["film, video"], "partof": ["civil rights history project", "american folklife center", "catalog"], "score": 34.297894, "shelf_id": "http://lccn.loc.gov/2016655401", "site": ["catalog"], "subject": ["oral histories", "ladner, dorie", "united states", "ladner, joyce a", "mississippi southern college", "alcorn state university", "national association for the advancement of colored people", "mississippi", "ku klux klan (1915- )", "personal narratives", "filmed interviews", "dahmer, ellie j.", "kennard, clyde", "african american women teachers", "interviews", "violence", "african american women civil rights workers", "race relations", "video recordings", "dahmer, vernon ferdinand", "civil rights movements", "voter registration", "african americans", "mississippi freedom project", "history", "hattiesburg", "segregation in education", "murder", "suffrage", "hattiesburg (miss.)"], "timestamp": "2022-10-17T14:38:46.135Z", "title": "Ellie Dahmer oral history interview conducted by Emilye Crosby in Hattiesburg, Mississippi, 2015 November 30", "type": ["moving image"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2016655401/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://lccn.loc.gov/2016655403", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2016655403/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.afc/afc2010039.afc2010039_crhp0112", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc2010039.afc2010039_crhp0112/", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc2010039.afc2010039_crhp0112_mv07/", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc2010039.afc2010039_crhp0112_ms01/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["smith, jeanette", "bishop, john melville", "branch, raylawni g.", "civil rights history project (u.s.)", "crosby, emilye"], "date": "2015-01-01", "dates": ["2015"], "description": ["Raylawni G. Branch and Jeanette Smith discuss their involvement in the Hattiesburg, Mississippi-based Civil Rights Movement. They remember their upbringings as mixed race children, Smith in Mississippi and Branch in Mississippi and Chicago, Illinois. Branch recalls entering as one of the first black students at the University of Southern Mississippi. Both speak about their activism for voting rights and education, as well as sharing their philosophies on issues of race, discrimination, and activism."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2022-10-04T17:35:53.116Z", "group": ["afc2010039", "catalog-split-00", "catalog", "civil-rights-history-project", "main-catalog-split-00", "main-catalog"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2016655403/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/afc/afc2010039/afc2010039_crhp0112/afc2010039_crhp0112_mv07.gif", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/afc/afc2010039/afc2010039_crhp0112/afc2010039_crhp0112_ms01.gif#h=150&w=116"], "index": 7, "language": ["english"], "location": ["united states", "mississippi", "hattiesburg"], "mime_type": ["image/gif", "application/pdf", "image/jpeg", "application/x-video"], "number": ["2016655403", "2020-02-20t15:36:11", "online resource"], "online_format": ["image", "pdf", "video"], "original_format": ["film, video"], "partof": ["civil rights history project", "american folklife center", "catalog"], "score": 34.297894, "shelf_id": "http://lccn.loc.gov/2016655403", "site": ["catalog"], "subject": ["smith, jeanette", "oral histories", "till, emmett", "united states", "school integration", "christianity", "william david)", "national association for the advancement of colored people", "mississippi", "personal narratives", "filmed interviews", "march on washington for jobs and freedom", "medical committee for human rights (u.s.)", "evers, charles", "mccain, william d.", "interviews", "branch, raylawni g.", "deacons for defense and justice", "african american women civil rights workers", "race relations", "video recordings", "dahmer, vernon ferdinand", "university of southern mississippi", "social justice", "head start program (u.s.)", "washington, d.c.)", "civil rights movements", "african americans", "student nonviolent coordinating committee (u.s.)", "mississippi freedom project", "religious aspects", "history", "council of federated organizations (u.s.)", "hattiesburg", "carmichael, stokely", "segregation in education", "suffrage", "hattiesburg (miss.)"], "timestamp": "2022-10-17T14:38:46.135Z", "title": "Raylawni G. Branch and Jeanette Smith oral history interview conducted by Emilye Crosby in Hattiesburg, Mississippi, 2015 December 01", "type": ["moving image"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2016655403/"}], "resource": {"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/msar/batch_msar_lapis_ver01/data/sn85044791/00383345066/1958050101/0407.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:msar:batch_msar_lapis_ver01:data:sn85044791:00383345066:1958050101:0406/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/msar/batch_msar_lapis_ver01/data/sn85044791/00383345066/1958050101/0407.pdf", "segment_count": 4, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn85044791/1958-05-01/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}, "resources": [{"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/msar/batch_msar_lapis_ver01/data/sn85044791/00383345066/1958050101/0407.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:msar:batch_msar_lapis_ver01:data:sn85044791:00383345066:1958050101:0406/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/msar/batch_msar_lapis_ver01/data/sn85044791/00383345066/1958050101/0407.pdf", "segment_count": 4, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn85044791/1958-05-01/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "segment_id": "/service/ndnp/msar/batch_msar_lapis_ver01/data/sn85044791/00383345066/1958050101/0407.xml", "segments": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn85044791/1958-05-01/ed-1/?sp=2"], "batch": ["msar_lapis_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/alabama/", "2/united states/alabama/baldwin/", "3/united states/alabama/baldwin/fairhope/", "1/united states/mississippi/", "2/united states/mississippi/forrest/", "3/united states/mississippi/forrest/petal/", "3/united states/mississippi/forrest/hattiesburg/"], "contributor": ["mississippi department of archives and history"], "date": "1958-05-01", "dates": ["1958-05-01"], "description": ["Potomac Continued from Preceding Page recession into a big depression The crisis that we are suffering is essentially a crisis of confi dence not simply one of profits The big bankers who control credit wont release it until they know what their cut interest is to be and what plans if any the government has for stimulating new production Thus far we have had two anti recession measures a big housing bill and a 1Vbillion increase for defense spending The latter of course is sheer waste For unex plained reasons the Administra tion would rather build arms and let them rust than help small un derdeveloped countries get on their feet Reports coming to the office of Vice President Nixon are that the public is growing a little tired of all this indecision by federal of ficials A little recession may be good for some people its ob viously quite good for the big commercial banks They have made a killing on the juggling cf interest rates But its no good for ordinary 1 _1 nn nnn fAP Rp ptupic CI1AVA o publican politicians Even Demo crats run a risk when things stay bad too long People get restive end"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2023-07-03T13:44:53.044Z", "group": ["ndnp/msar", "mississippi-department-of-archives-and-history"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn85044791/1958-05-01/ed-1/?sp=2", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:msar:batch_msar_lapis_ver01:data:sn85044791:00383345066:1958050101:0407/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=459&w=301", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:msar:batch_msar_lapis_ver01:data:sn85044791:00383345066:1958050101:0407/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=918&w=603", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/msar/batch_msar_lapis_ver01/data/sn85044791/00383345066/19